   <concept id="FAR_6_302_5" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">6.302-5</ph> Authorized or required
by statute.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d384e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Authority.</p>
               <ol id="d384e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Citations: 
                           <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3204&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 3204(a)(5)</xref>
                           
                         or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3304(a)(5)&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3304(a)(5)</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e27">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Full and
open competition need not be provided for when–</p>
                     <ol id="d384e48" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e33">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> A statute
expressly authorizes or requires that the acquisition be made through
another agency or from a specified source; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e38">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> The agency’s
need is for a brand name commercial
product for authorized resale.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e43">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Application</i>.
This authority may be used when statutes, such as the following,
expressly authorize or require that acquisition be made from a specified
source or through another agency:</p>
               <ol id="d384e83" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e51">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Federal Prison
Industries (UNICOR) <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title18-section4124&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">18 U.S.C. 4124</xref> (see <xref href="Subpart_8.6.dita#FAR_Subpart_8_6"
                              base="i1117091"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.6</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e62">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Qualified
nonprofit agencies for the blind or other severely disabled <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid%3AUSC-prelim-title41-chapter85&amp;saved=%7CZ3JhbnVsZWlkOlVTQy1wcmVsaW0tdGl0bGU0MC1jaGFwdGVyMzctZnJvbnQ%3D%7C%7C%7C0%7Cfalse%7Cprelim&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. chapter 85</xref>, Committee
for Purchase From People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled (see <xref href="Subpart_8.7.dita#FAR_Subpart_8_7"
                              base="i1116916"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.7</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e73">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Government
Printing and Binding <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title44-section501&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">44 U.S.C. 501</xref>-<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title44-section504&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">504</xref>,
1121 (see <xref href="Subpart_8.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_8_8"
                              base="i1116866"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.8</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e84">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Sole source awards under the 8(a) Program (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title15-section637&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 637</xref>), but see <xref href="6.303.dita#FAR_6_303"
                              base="i1119735"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.303</xref> for requirements for justification and approval of sole-source 8(a) awards over <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$30 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 6.302-5 in paragraphs (b)(4) and (c)(2)(iii) by removing “$25 million” and adding “$30 million” in their places, respectively.?></ph>. (See subpart <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.8</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e95">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph> Sole source
awards under the HUBZone Act of 1997-<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title15-section657a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 657a</xref> (see <xref href="19.1306.dita#FAR_19_1306"
                              base="i1099639"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1306</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e106">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph> Sole source
awards under the Veterans Benefits Act of 2003 (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title15-section657f&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 657f</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="i1119663" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e114">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph> Sole
source awards under the WOSB Program– <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title15-section637(m)&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 637(m)</xref> (see <xref href="19.1506.dita#FAR_19_1506"
                              base="i1099284"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1506</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e125">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> Limitations.</p>
               <ol id="d384e198" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e131">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> This
authority shall not be used when a provision of law requires an
agency to award a new contract to a specified non-Federal Government
entity unless the provision of law specifically—</p>
                     <ol id="d384e208" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e137">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Identifies
the entity involved;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e142">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Refers to 
                                 <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3201&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 3201(e)</xref>
                                 
                               for armed services acquisitions or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3105&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    scope="external"
                                    format="html"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3105</xref> for civilian agency acquisitions; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e153">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> States
that award to that entity shall be made in contravention of the
merit-based selection procedures in <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section2304(k)&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    scope="external"
                                    format="html"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2304(k)</xref> or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3105&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    scope="external"
                                    format="html"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3105</xref>, as
appropriate. However, this limitation does not apply–</p>
                           <ol id="d384e248" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e165">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph> When
the work provided for in the contract is a continuation of the work
performed by the specified entity under a preceding contract; or</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e170">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph> To any
contract requiring the National Academy of Sciences to investigate,
examine, or experiment upon any subject of science or art of significance
to an executive agency and to report on those matters to the Congress or
any agency of the Federal Government.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e175">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Contracts
awarded using this authority shall be supported by the written justifications
and approvals described in <xref href="6.303.dita#FAR_6_303"
                              base="i1119735"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.303</xref> and <xref href="6.304.dita#FAR_6_304"
                              base="i1119818"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>, except for–</p>
                     <ol id="d384e286" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e187">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Contracts
awarded under (a)(2)(ii) or (b)(2) of this section;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e192">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Contracts
awarded under (a)(2)(i) of this section when the statute expressly
requires that the procurement be made from a specified source. (Justification
and approval requirements apply when the statute authorizes, but
does not require, that the procurement be made from a specified
source); or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e197">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> Contracts less than or equal to <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$30 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 6.302-5 in paragraphs (b)(4) and (c)(2)(iii) by removing “$25 million” and adding “$30 million” in their places, respectively.?></ph> awarded under (b)(4) of this section.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d398e202">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> The authority
in (a)(2)(ii) of this section may be used only for purchases of brand name commercial products for resale
through commissaries or other similar facilities. Ordinarily, these
purchases will involve articles desired or preferred by customers
of the selling activities (but see <xref href="6.301.dita#FAR_6_301"
                              base="i1119438"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.301</xref>(d)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
